pull_request.title: BIKE and Picnic enablement for cygwin
pull_request.body:
Resolves some issues in #1000 as per input from @jschanck . Will eliminate caveats in https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/wiki/Platform-specific-notes-for-building-liboqs#using-cygwin.

* [ ] Does this PR change the input/output behaviour of a cryptographic algorithm (i.e., does it change known answer test values)?  (If so, a version bump will be required from *x.y.z* to *x.(y+1).0*.)
* [ ] Does this PR change the the list of algorithms available -- either adding, removing, or renaming?  (If so, PRs in OQS-OpenSSL, OQS-BoringSSL, and OQS-OpenSSH will also be required by the time this is merged.)

pull_request.title: Validating proper internal cmake option use
pull_request.body:
Use cmake options as explicit variables including CI test checking for inadvertently uninitialized `cmake` variables.

Fixes #865.

This applies to all options *not* generated and used internally (i.e., true constants from [oqsconfig.h](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/blob/main/src/oqsconfig.h.cmake)).

Going forward, all contributors are asked to only use --at least for all options [documented in the Wiki](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/wiki/Customizing-liboqs)-- the `cmake` variable notation "${VARIABLE}" instead of the "short-form" (constant) "VARIABLE" in boolean expressions in `cmake` files.

Also, all options [documented in the Wiki](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/wiki/Customizing-liboqs) now have proper `cmake -LAH` documentation output (for those not reading Wikis :).

* [ ] Does this PR change the input/output behaviour of a cryptographic algorithm (i.e., does it change known answer test values)?  (If so, a version bump will be required from *x.y.z* to *x.(y+1).0*.)
* [ ] Does this PR change the the list of algorithms available -- either adding, removing, or renaming?  (If so, PRs in OQS-OpenSSL, OQS-BoringSSL, and OQS-OpenSSH will also be required by the time this is merged.)
